The paper deals with content-based medical image retrieval, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also introduces a new method for encoding image content using binary vectors, which falls under machine learning (cs.MM), deep learning (cs.DL), and machine learning (cs.LG). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.IR, followed by cs.MM, cs.DL, and cs.LG.
